<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="643" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d643">
                            <head>No. 641.<lb/><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-11-21"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 21,
                                        1873</date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Constant efforts are made by this cabinet to conciliate England.
                                Castelar is every day at the British legation. The press has
                                received an official hint to contrast the moderation of England with
                                our impatience. I suspect overtures have been made also to Germany
                                for her good offices.</p>
                            <closer><signed>SICKLES.</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>